  <text>
    <body>
	<p>Produced by <persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/27072443">Tristan Tzara</persName> as a response to attacks on him by <persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/36923084">Francis Picabia</persName> and <persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/49222341">André Breton</persName> about the future of the <rs>Dada</rs> movement. Printed in black on pale pink stock, with typographic and pictorial collage cover. Literary contributors included <persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/73848255">Paul Éluard</persName>, Georges Ribemont-Dessaignes, and <persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88805508">Erik Satie</persName>. Cover design attributed to <persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/31997865">Iliazd</persName>.</p>
